text.section:
An operator shall, upon receiving an emergency locate request or a normal excavation locate request:
Inform the excavator of the approximate location and description of any of the operator's facilities that may be damaged or pose a safety concern because of excavation or demolition;
Inform the excavator of any other information that would assist in locating and avoiding contact with or damage to underground facilities;
Unless permanent facility markers are provided, provide temporary markings to inform the excavator of the ownership and approximate location of the underground facility; and
Notify the requesting party if underground facilities are not in conflict with the excavation or demolition.
